                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="275r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Mariginal additions by several different hands from different periods in the form of manicules, signs, corrections, and comments. The additions are not very frequent and usually only consist of one word. Many of the corrections appear to be by the scribe or a contemporary hand.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="8rb" to="8rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>face added to letter A.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in black ink, capitals touched in yellow, rubrics in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1ra" to="1ra" scheme="folios"/>: Foliate initial U over 7 lines (+ extending in the margin). The letter is placed in a blue frame with gold edges, the counter space is gilded and filled with a curled vegetative shape with two leaves and fox’s (?) head. Part of the frame or letter extends along the inner margin and half of the bottom margin. Main colours pink, blue, and red. The inital is followed by a smaller capital penwork N over 2 lines in black and touched in yellow. <locus from="1rb" to="273rb" scheme="folios"/>: plain initals over 2-3 lines in blue or red with red, blue and/or green flourishing, which sometimes extends along the entire margin. The initial is followed by a capital touched in yellow, occasionally these capitals inlcude some penwork details, e.g. <locus from="32va" to="32va" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
